1.2 Aesthetic:

3aes()3color, shapesize

colorshapesize

#classcolor = class 
ggplot(mpg, aes(displ, hwy, col = class)) + 
  geom_point()

#drvshape = drv  
ggplot(mpg, aes(displ, hwy, shape = drv, color = class)) + 
  geom_point()

#cylsize = cyl 
ggplot(mpg, aes(displ, hwy, size = cyl)) + 
  geom_point()

1.3 Facet

  facet_wrap(~drv)

2 pipe operator

Ctrl+Shift+M

#mpg ggplot()
mpg %>% ggplot(aes(displ, hwy,color = class)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  facet_wrap(~drv)

#mpg ggplot()
mpg %>% filter(year==2008) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(displ, hwy,color = class)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  facet_wrap(~drv)

#filter()
mpg %>% filter(class == "compact" | class == "suv") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(displ, hwy,color = class)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  facet_wrap(~drv)

3.1 

mpg %>% ggplot(aes(manufacturer)) + 
  geom_bar(col = 5, fill = 5)

3.2 

#fct_infreq() 
#
mpg %>% ggplot(aes(fct_infreq(manufacturer))) + 
  geom_bar(col = 6, fill = 6)+
  guides(x = guide_axis(angle = 90))

#
mpg %>% ggplot(aes(fct_infreq(manufacturer))) + 
  geom_bar(col = 5, fill = 5)+
  geom_text(stat = "count", aes(label = after_stat(count)), vjust = -0.5)

3.3 

mpg %>% ggplot(aes(fct_infreq(class))) + 
  geom_bar(col = 6, fill = 6)+
  facet_wrap(~year)

# position = "dodge"  side by side bar plot 
mpg %>%
filter(manufacturer == "ford"|manufacturer == "toyota") %>%
  ggplot(aes(manufacturer,fill = class))+
  geom_bar(position = "dodge",alpha=0.5)+
  theme_bw()+
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
  panel.grid.minor = element_blank())+
  labs(title = "Class and Manufacturer",
  x = "manufacturer",
  y = "Number")

3.4 

#position = "fill" 
mpg %>%
filter(manufacturer == "ford"|manufacturer == "toyota") %>%
  ggplot(aes(manufacturer,fill = class))+
  geom_bar(position = "fill",alpha=0.5)+
  theme_bw()+
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
  panel.grid.minor = element_blank())+
  labs(title = "Class and Manufacturer",
  x = "manufacturer",
  y = "Number")

`stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

  ggplot(aes(cty))+

#facet_wrap

  ggplot(aes(cty,col = transmission))+
  geom_boxplot()+
  facet_wrap(~transmission)+
  coord_flip()

mpg %>% 
  ggplot(aes(cty,hwy,col = transmission,size=cyl,alpha=0.3))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_smooth(method = lm, se = F)+
  facet_wrap(~transmission)+
  theme_bw()+
  theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
  panel.grid.minor = element_blank())+
  labs(title = "Fuel Economy in City & Highway",
  x = "city miles per gallon",
  y = "highway miles per gallon")
